title: Artists and poets - Greenwich Village.

139-131 Mac Dougal Street, west side, between West 4th and 3rd Streets. No. 137 being the Open Door Restaurant. Note the Art Exhibit; a semi-annual event in the "Village".

May 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

The same viewing northward. The Provincetown Playhouse is located at 133 and is being used at this date as a W. P. A. Federal Theatre.

September 22, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

A set of 2, consisting of a positive and a negative view of the Provincetown Playhouse, No. 133.
